    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <date>11 March 1856</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir—</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I send you the corrected list of Podophthalma—</p>
                  <p>I quite agree with you in liking the appearance of the Journal— I believe it has hitherto given satisfaction— but it had nearly been a bad bone of contention at first—</p>
                  <p>Your allusion to Lester’s intended journey to Egypt is the first intimation I have had of his intention— I have not seen him since he came to London, where I understood he proposed remaining for about 3 months to take a course of Chemistry— He is a very promising young man, and must have a great deal of good purpose in him to have achieved such a victory over his early habits—</p>
                  <p>Believe me| yours very truly | Thomas Bell</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
